:"48311100","scheme":"CPV"},{"id":"32321200","scheme":"CPV"},{"id":"50300000","scheme":"CPV"},{"id":"72000000","scheme":"CPV"},{"id":"72100000","scheme":"CPV"},{"id":"72130000","scheme":"CPV"},{"id":"72220000","scheme":"CPV"},{"id":"72222000","scheme":"CPV"},{"id":"72222300","scheme":"CPV"},{"id":"72223000","scheme":"CPV"},{"id":"72224000","scheme":"CPV"},{"id":"72224100","scheme":"CPV"},{"id":"72227000","scheme":"CPV"}],"deliveryLocation":{"description":"Pan-Wales"},"deliveryAddresses":[{"region":"UKL"}],"relatedLot":"5"}],"value":{"amount":200000000.0,"currency":"GBP"},"procurementMethod":"open","procurementMethodDetails":"Open procedure","mainProcurementCategory":"goods","submissionMethod":["electronicSubmission"],"submissionMethodDetails":"https://etenderwales.bravosolution.co.uk","tenderPeriod":{"endDate":"2025-04-29T12:00:00Z"},"awardPeriod":{"startDate":"2025-04-30T09:00:00Z"},"documents":[{"id":"FEB497854","documentType":"contractNotice","title":"WGCD IT Products and Services Agreement (iii)","description":"The Welsh Government Commercial Delivery Team, on behalf of the Welsh Public Sector, wishes to establish a collaborative Framework Agreement for the supply of IT Product and Services to the public sector in Wales.rn There will be five lots to covering a range of Products and/ or Services as follows:rn Lot 1 - Hardwarern Lot 2 - Softwarern Lot 3 - Audio Visual Servicesrn Lot 4 - Multi-functional Print Devices and Print Solutionsrn Lot 5 - Integrated Solutions","url":"https://www.sell2wales.gov.wales/search/show/search_view.aspx?ID=FEB497854","format":"text/html"},{"id":"economic","documentType":"economicSelectionCriteria"},{"id":"technical","documentType":"technicalSelectionCriteria"}],"lots":[{"id":"4","title":"Multi-Functional Print Devices and Print Solutions","description":"The Supplier shall be required to provide a range of Products and/ or Services under this lot:rn Multi-Functional Print Devices and Print Solutionsrn The objective of this framework is to:rn (a) Provide Customers with a wide range of MFD products and services, which meet the individual Customers requirements;rn (b) Offer a flexible, competitive and simple route to market;rn (c) Provide a value for money route to market, which continues to evolve to offer the latest technologies at competitive pricing; andrn (d) Provide document and print solutions which balance the need for immediate savings, whilst considering the socio and environmental impact on future generations.. A maximum of 8 suppliers will be awarded a place within this Lot.rn Suppliers successful under this Lot will be provided the option to be appointed to Lot 5 (Integrated Solutions).","status":"active","awardCriteria":{"criteria":[{"type":"quality","name":"Technical","description":"70%"},{"type":"price","description":"30%"}]},"hasOptions":false,"submissionTerms":{"variantPolicy":"notAllowed"},"contractPeriod":{"durationInDays":1440},"hasRenewal":false},{"id":"1","title":"Hardware","description":"The purpose of this Lot is to provide Customers with:rn (a) access to a wide range of IT Hardware products;rn (b) access to services to support, manage and enable IT hardware estates;rn (c) value for money, through;rn (i) an effective supply chain;rn (ii) supply base with Vendor Accreditations; andrn (iii) value added services.rn The Supplier shall provide a range of IT Hardware, including but not limited to;rn (a) end user devices;rn (b) servers and storage devices;rn (c) network equipment;rn (d) converged infrastructure;rn (e) Electronic Point of Sale (EPOS hardware); andrn (f) end point devices.. A maximum of 15 suppliers will be awarded a place within this Lot.rn Suppliers successful under this Lot will be provided the option to be appointed to Lot 5 (Integrated Solutions).","status":"active","awardCriteria":{"criteria":[{"type":"quality","name":"Technical","description":"70%"},{"type":"price","description":"30%"}]},"hasOptions":false,"submissionTerms":{"variantPolicy":"notAllowed"},"contractPeriod":{"durationInDays":1440},"hasRenewal":false},{"id":"2","title":"Software","description":"The purpose of this Lot is to provide Customers:rn (a) access to a wide range of software and cloud services products;rn (b) access to services to deploy and manage software and cloud services;rn (c) value for money, through;rn (i) competitive tendering (further competitions);rn (ii) supply base with Vendor Accreditations; andrn (iii) value adding services.rn Licensing and Subscription Scopern The Supplier shall provide a wide range of licensing and subscriptions, including but not limited to:rn (a) off-the-shelf software licences;rn (b) enterprise licenses;rn (c) open source software;rn (d) Software as a Service subscriptions;rn (e) support licence renewals; andrn (f) cloud and web services (including Platform and Infrastructure as a Service).rn The Supplier shall have the capability to provide software products to multiple operating systems.rn Associated Services Scopern The Supplier shall provide a range of design, implementation and on-going management Services, to include but not be limited to:rn (a) strategy design;rn (b) security management. A maximum of 8 suppliers will be awarded a place within this Lot.rn Suppliers successful under this Lot will be provided the option to be appointed to Lot 5 (Integrated Solutions).","status":"active","awardCriteria":{"criteria":[{"type":"quality","name":"Technical","description":"70%"},{"type":"price","description":"30%"}]},"hasOptions":false,"submissionTerms":{"variantPolicy":"notAllowed"},"contractPeriod":{"durationInDays":1440},"hasRenewal":false},{"id":"3","title":"Audio Visual Services","description":"The Supplier shall provide a range of Audio Visual Services equipment including but not limited to:rn (a) video conferencing equipment;rn (b) interactive whiteboards;rn (c) interactive displays;rn (d) projectors;rn (e) sound and visual recording equipment;rn (f) CCTV systems;rn (g) meeting room audio;rn (h) PA systems; andrn (i) digital signage etc.rn The Supplier shall be able to provide rental equipment and services for instances such as one-off events.rn Servicesrn The Supplier shall be required to provide on-going support and maintenance for:rn (a) equipment installed by the Supplier; andrn (b) existing equipment.. A maximum of 5 suppliers will be awarded a place within this Lot.rn Tenderers bidding for Lot 3 (Audio Visual) shall not be permitted to bid for any other Lots, with the exception of the option of being appointed to Lot 5 (Integrated Solutions)","status":"active","awardCriteria":{"criteria":[{"type":"quality","name":"Technical","description":"70%"},{"type":"price","description":"30%"}]},"hasOptions":false,"submissionTerms":{"variantPolicy":"notAllowed"},"contractPeriod":{"durationInDays":1440},"hasRenewal":false},{"id":"5","title":"Integrated Solutions","description":"The Supplier shall provide an integrated IT Hardware and Software Solutions service, which will include but will not be limited to the scope of Lots 1 – 4.rn This may take the form of:rn (a) a one-stop-shop solution in which a single Supplier provides all aspects of the Customers IT requirements;rn (i) several Elements, i.e. Hardware & Softwarern (ii) semi managed service, where a supplier would provide day-to-day operations, such as schools appointing a supplier to provide, install and manage network, to support Chrome/ Apple etc. orrn (b) the design, implementation and/ or support of an IT Solution, which requires Products and or Services covered by 2 or more Lots, including but not limited to:rn (i) digital Transformationrn (ii) emerging Technologies, i.e. Smart City, machine learning, IoTrn (iii) unified/ corporate comms;rn (iv) converged/ hyper converged/ software defined Infrastructure;rn (v) data centre design and implementation;rn (vi) hybrid infrastructure solutions; andrn (vii) bundled hardware and software.rn (viii) audio Visual Solutionsrn (ix) print and document solutionsrn Successful Tenderers on Lot 1 (Hardware), Lot 2 (Software), Lot 3 (Audio Visual Services) and Lot 4 (Multi-Functional Print Devices and Print Solutions) shall automatically be given the option to be appointed to Lot 5 (Integrated Solutions).. A maximum of 36 suppliers will be awarded a place within this Lot.rn For avoidance of doubt, there will be no separate Tender exercise to appoint Tenderers to Lot 5 (Integrated Solutions).","status":"active","hasOptions":false,"submissionTerms":{"variantPolicy":"notAllowed"},"contractPeriod":{"durationInDays":1440},"hasRenewal":false}],"lotDetails":{"maximumLotsBidPerSupplier":2147483647},"bidOpening":{"date":"2025-04-30T09:00:00Z","address":{"streetAddress":"Virtual"},"description":"WGCD Team"},"communication":{"atypicalToolUrl":"https://etenderwales.bravosolution.co.uk"},"contractTerms":{"hasElectronicPayment":true,"hasElectronicOrdering":true,"electronicInvoicingPolicy":"allowed"},"coveredBy":["GPA"],"submissionTerms":{"languages":["en","cy"],"bidValidityPeriod":{"durationInDays":180}},"techniques":{"hasFrameworkAgreement":true,"frameworkAgreement":{"maximumParticipants":36.0}},"classification":{"id":"30200000","scheme":"CPV"},"hasRecurrence":false,"legalBasis":{"id":"32014L0024","scheme":"CELEX"}},"language":"EN","relatedProcesses":[{"id":"1","relationship":["planning"],"scheme":"EU-OJ","identifier":"2024/S 000-034328"}],"description":"The Invitation to Tender (ITT) documentation can be accessed via eTenderWales,rn The eTenderWales Project references for this framework is Project_58579.rn Within the project there is one ITT Qualification Questionnaire and one ITT Technical Questionnaire that ALL bidders must complete irrespective of the Lot/s you are bidding for. There are four separate ITT Commercial Questionnaires. Bidders only need to complete the ITT that relates to the lot/s they are bidding for.rn Click on the Project title to access summary details of the ITT. If you are still interested in submitting a tender, click the ‘Express an Interest button’. This will move the ITT from the ‘Open to all Suppliers’ area to the ‘My ITT's’ on the home page.rn You will then see the full details of the ITT in the qualification and technical envelopes along with any relevant documents in the ‘Attachments’ area.rn If you have any queries regarding the tender please message using the e-TenderWales message portal.rn If you require the documentation in an alternative format, please use the ‘Messages’ area to contact the buyer directly, who will be able to provide a more suitable format. For example, Braille, Large Print, Word Document or Audio format.rn Please note that recording your interest on does not automatically enter you into the tender process for this notice.rn NOTE: The authority is using eTenderwales to carry out this procurement process. To obtain further information record your interest on Sell2Wales at http://www.sell2wales.gov.wales/search/search_switch.aspx?ID=148098rn Under the terms of this contract the successful supplier(s) will be required to deliver Community Benefits in support of the authority’s economic and social objectives. Accordingly, contract performance conditions may relate in particular to social and environmental considerations. The Community Benefits included in this contract are:rn (a)Training and recruitment of economically inactive people: Creating new opportunities such as apprenticeships or providing hands on training weeks for current apprentices; intermediate training or work experience opportunities such as Traineeships; Work Trials or ‘sandwich’ placements for in-study work experience.rn (b)Supply chain initiatives and Working with the 3rd Sector: Promotion of open and accessible supply chains that provide opportunities, for Wales based businesses - especially those who form part of our Foundational Economy and SMEs - to bid for work; promote engagement with social enterprises and supported businesses; promotion of fair work and prompt and fair payment terms down supply chains. Taking a circular approach to shorten supply chains can improve efficiency, create employment and increase competitiveness.rn (c)Educational initiatives: Contributions to education in Wales through engagement with school, college and university curriculums focused on supporting STEM learning.rn (d)Community and cultural initiatives: Contributions to community initiatives including those that support tackling poverty across Wales and that leave a lasting legacy within the community; promote attendance and participation in community and cultural events and that protect our cultural heritage. Moving to a circular economy can benefit our economy by retaining value in more resilient and shorter supply chains and enabling people and communities to come together to share resources and revitalise where we live.rn (e)Environmental initiatives: Taking opportunities to minimise the environmental impact of the contract and to maximise the environmental benefits, especially where these objectives cannot be made part of the specification.rn (WA Ref:148098)rn The buyer considers that this contract is suitable for consortia.","links":[{"rel":"canonical","href":"https://api.sell2wales.gov.wales/v1?lang=cy/Notice?id=ocds-kuma6s-148098"}]}
